String Literal A string literal is used to create a string value. A string literal consists of a sequence of zero or more Unicode Code Points.
✍ Syntax Double Quoted String Literal &quot; StringCharacters* &quot;
Here StringCharacters is an Unicode Code Point except 0xA | 0xD | \ | &quot;
Read More ✍ Syntax String Escape \t | \n | \r | \\ | \&quot;
Read More ✍ Syntax Numeric Escape u{ Digit+ }
